{{Infobox writer | name = Bob van Luijt | image = Bob van Luijt @ SXSW 2018.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = Bob van Luijt at SXSW 2018 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1985|11|15}} | birth_place = [[Bergen op Zoom]], The Netherlands. | education = [[Artez|Artez Institute of the Arts]] | occupation = Technologist, designer, entrepreneur, artist, composer and new media artist | nationality = Dutch | notableworks = {{Plainlist| * [[Control(human, data, sound)]]'' * ''[[The Core (album)|The Core]]'' }} | website = {{URL|bob.wtf|bob.wtf}} }}
'''Bob van Luijt''' (born 15 November 1985 in [[Bergen op Zoom]]{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}) is a technologist,<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://trendnomad.com/music-in-your-head|title=Music in your head|work=TrendNomad|date=21 August 2015|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> designer,<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://dmyberlin.com/en/festival_2015/central_exhibition/kubrickology-bob-van-luijt|title=Bob van Luijt about Strategic Design at Berlin Design Week|work=Berlin Design Week|date=13 June 2015|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> founder, composer and [[new media artist]] from the [[Netherlands]]. He is the founder of design and technology firm [[Kubrickology (company)|Kubrickology]] and the chairman of the [[Creative Software Foundation (foundation)|Creative Software Foundation]].
==Technology== [[File:Kubrickology at the Dutch Design Week.jpg|thumb|Kubrickology at the [[Dutch Design Week]] in the [[Van Abbemuseum]]]]
[[Control(human, data, sound)]] (CHDS)<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://chds.io/|title=control(human, data, sound)|date=2015|language=en}}</ref> was his first tech-based artwork and was selected as an awards Finalist for [[Three_Rivers_Arts_Festival|CREATE]] 2015 in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States, in the category art+technology.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.nextpittsburgh.com/events/create-2015-pittsburghs-art-technology-festival/|title=Create 2015|date=2015|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://renateroze.com/films/my-latest-co-produced-project-controlhuman-data-sound/|title=Weblog about CHDS|date=2015|language=en}}</ref> In March 2016<ref>[https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate/graphs/contributors Weaviate on Github]</ref> he started an open source project called [[Weaviate]],<ref>[https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate Weaviate on Github]</ref> which is a decentralised, [[Semantic_Web|semantic]], Web of Things platform which is used to connect and relate all things from the physical world.
==Music== Van Luijt received a bachelor's degree from [[Artez|Artez Institute of the Arts]]. After completing his studies he created notable works that include [[The Core (album)|The Core]].<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.allaboutjazz.com/the-core-bob-van-luijt-kubrickology-music-review-by-bruce-lindsay.php?width=1600|title=Bob Van Luijt's Square Orange: The Core|work=All About Jazz|date=3 March 2014|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> He collaborated on [[harpist]] [[Anne Vanschothorst]]'s album ''Ek is eik''.,<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://8weekly.nl/recensie/muziek/anne-vanschothorst-ek-is-eik-muziek-voor-een-open-geest/|title=Muziek voor een open geest|work=8 Weekly|date=8 May 2014|language=nl|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> with [[Billy Martin]] and [[Florian Weber]]<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FrkgL5ibF1I|title=Florian Weber, Bob van Luijt & Billy Martin|date=3 March 2014|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref> and with [[Yonga Sun]] and [[Cuong Vu]].<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.londonjazznews.com/2012/02/review-cuong-vu.html|title=Review: Cuong Vu, Bob van Luijt and Yonga Sun|date=3 February 2012|accessdate=5 July 2016}}</ref>
==Blog== Van Luijt's "explorations on the developments in technology, art, and design"<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://bob.wtf|title=blog|accessdate=15 October 2017}}</ref> can be found on his blog "Bob’s WTF blog" and form the source of frequent lectures at conferences<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://gdg-north.ru/speakers/4|title=Google Developers Conference Saint Petersburg}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.ndbsevents.com/rk_speaker/bob-van-luijt/|title=Nordic Digital Business Summit}}</ref> and universities<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.tilburguniversity.edu/current/Art-Talks-Moyra-Besjes-Bob-van-Luijt/|title=Art Talks Tilburg University}}</ref> throughout Europe, the US, and Russia.
