'''Neemat Georges Frem''' ({{lang-ar|نعمة ج. افرام}}) is a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] businessman, and a [[Parliament of Lebanon|member of the parliament of Lebanon]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elnashra.com/news/show/1161659/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1:-%D9%81%D8%B4%D9%84-%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D8%B6%D9%85-%D9%86%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A6|title=الأخبار: فشل محاولات القوات بضم نعمة افرام إلى لائحتها في دائرة كسروان|work=Elnashra News|access-date=2017-12-22|language=ar-AR}}</ref> He is former president of the [[Association of Lebanese Industrialists]], chief executive of the multinational company [[INDEVCO Group]],<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.executive-magazine.com/economics-policy/qa-neemat-frem|title=Q&A – Neemat Frem|date=2011-08-03|work=Executive Magazine|access-date=2018-01-17|language=en-US}}</ref> and founder and president of Phoenix Machinery.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cruxnow.com/global-church/2017/10/28/unique-lebanon-shows-refugees-need-safe-zones-syria/|title=Unique Lebanon shows why refugees need safe zones in Syria|date=2017-10-28|work=Crux|access-date=2017-12-22|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.clfw.org/about-us-bios.html|title=About CLFW- Bios|website=www.clfw.org|access-date=2018-01-17}}</ref> He is also the current President of The Maronite Foundation in the World.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indefenseofchristians.org/idc-2017-summit/|title=IDC 2017 Summit - In Defense of Christians|work=In Defense of Christians|access-date=2018-01-10|language=en-US}}</ref> Frem was elected [[Parliament of Lebanon|member of parliament]] in Jbeil and Keserwan constituency during the [[Lebanese general election, 2018|Lebanese general election]] held in Lebanon on 6 May 2018.
==Early life and education== Frem was born on 10 September 1967 in [[Jounieh]], [[Keserwan]] of [[Lebanon]]. Frem completed school at [[Collège Saint Joseph – Antoura]]. He graduated from [[American University of Beirut]] with a Bachelor degree in Electrical Engineering in 1991.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=http://nac2016.org/speakers/neemat-frem/|title=Neemat Frem « NAC 2016|website=nac2016.org}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> He completed postgraduate diploma on leadership and business from [[Harvard University Business School]], [[Georgetown University Business School]] and [[Stanford University|Stanford University Business School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seulementpourvip.com/Winter2017/22neematfrem.php|title=Seulement Pour VIP|website=www.seulementpourvip.com}}</ref>
== Career== [[File:Frem at research and strategic studies center 3.jpg|left|thumb|Frem at Research and Strategic Studies Center of Lebanon]]
Currently, Frem serves as a deputy in the Lebanese Parliament representing Keserwan and Jbeil electoral district. He also serves as the president and chief executive officer (CEO) of INDEVCO Group that manages 60 operations including 37 manufacturing plants and 23 commercial companies around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=44267727&privcapId=27991042|title=Neemat G. Frem: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|website=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref> The group also runs 20 subsidiaries in other countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.executive-magazine.com/economics-policy/qa-neemat-frem|title=Q&A – Neemat Frem|date=3 August 2011|publisher=}}</ref> He served as the CEO of Interstate Resources, Inc.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://magazine.com.lb/index.php/fr/mobile/item/8106-neemat-frem-vice-pr%C3%A9sident-de-la-fondation-maronite-la-situation-actuelle-est-grave?issue_id=132|title=Neemat Frem, vice-président de la Fondation maronite.|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2018-01-04|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=fr}}</ref> He was elected as the President of the Association of Lebanese Industrialists (ALI) in 2010 and served till 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessnews.com.lb/cms/Story/StoryDetails.aspx?ItemID=5963|title=Industrial production reported at $8.8 billion. Industrial indicators launched|website=BusinessNews.com.lb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebusinessyear.com/lebanon-2014/march-of-the-machines/interview|title=March Of The Machines|website=The Business Year|access-date=2018-01-04}}</ref> He holds one [[United States|US]] and one [[Europe]] [[patent]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.google.ch/patents/US7281468|title=Automatic sandwich dispenser and method for automatically dispensing sandwiches|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=https://encrypted.google.com/patents/EP1339029A1?cl=pt-PT|title=Patent EP1339029A1 - Distributeur automatique de sandwichs et procédé de distribution automatique de sandwichs|date=21 February 2002|publisher=|journal=Google Books}}</ref> In 2013, he launched "A Better Lebanon" initiative, generating public policies by empowering national public, private and civil society institutions as an attempt for a restructuring change in the Lebanese continuous political crisis.<ref name=":1" />
=== Political career === In 2018, Frem announced his candidacy for the Lebanese General Election, running for the Maronite seat in the Keserwan and Jbeil constituency. Following the general election held on 6 May 2018, he was officially announced as a winning candidate.
