{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Segun Abraham | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = 220px | alt = | caption = A 2015 portrait of Segun Abraham | birth_name = Olusegun Abraham | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1953|12|24}} | birth_place = [[Ikare|Ikare-Akoko]], [[Ondo State]], [[Nigeria]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}}(death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | burial_place = <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays "Burial place" as label) --> | nationality = [[Nigerian]] | other_names = | alma_mater = {{plainlist| *[[Tyndale University College and Seminary]] *[[Institute of Directors]]}} | occupation = {{flatlist| *[[Politician]] *[[businessman]]}} | years_active = 1999&ndash;present | known_for = | notable_works = <!-- produces label "Notable work"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label "Notable credit(s)"; or by |works=, which produces label "Works" --> | home_town = | party = [[All Progressives Congress]] | spouse = Bunmi Abraham | children = | awards = | website = {{URL|segunabraham.com}} | module = | signature = | signature_size = | signature_alt = | footnotes = }}
'''Olusegun Abraham''' (born {{birth date|1953|12|24}}) is a Nigerian [[politician]] and [[business mogul]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/politics/5644-ondo_governorship_acn_shortlists_three_candidate.html|title=Ondo governorship: CAN shortlists three candidates, drops Agunloye, others|work=[[Premium Times]]|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/why-i-want-to-govern-ondo-by-abraham/|title=Why I want to govern Ondo, by Abraham|work=[[The Nation (Nigeria)|The Nation]]|last=Oladesu|first=Emmanuel|date=21 December 2015|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Olusegun was born and raised in [[Ikare|Ikare-Akoko]], [[Ondo State]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://citynews.ng/ondo-2016-likely-political-gladiators-for-governorship-seat/|title=Ondo 2016: Likely political gladiators for governorship seat|work=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post Newspaper]]|last=Badejo|first=Abiodun|date=12 August 2015|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> where he had his early formal education. He holds a master's degree in [[Technology management]]. He has also undertaken professional courses in notable institutions including [[Tyndale University College and Seminary]], [[Canada]] and the [[Institute of Directors]], [[United Kingdom]].
==Career== In 1999, Segun Abraham delved into politics while managing his business ventures simultaneously.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://citypeopleng.com/why-i-had-to-step-down-for-akeredolu-in-2012/|title=OLUSEGUN ABRAHAM: “Why I Had To Step Down For AKEREDOLU In 2012”|work=City People Magazine|last=Shittu|first=Adeola|date=6 February 2016|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> He was one of the pioneering members of the [[All Progressives Congress]] when it was still called [[Alliance for Democracy (Nigeria)|Alliance for Democracy]]. Olusegun was also one of those who campaigned for former Governor [[Adebayo Adefarati]]. He went on to be appointed the chairman of Owena Hotels by Adebayo Farati until the hotel was bought by Oodua Investment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.m.thenigerianvoice.com/news/88872/1/ill-adopt-awos-innovative-ideas-abraham-acn-aspirant.html|title=I’LL ADOPT AWO’S INNOVATIVE IDEAS – ABRAHAM, CAN ASPIRANT|work=Nigerian Best Forum|publisher=The Nigerian Voice|date=2 May 2012|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref>
In 2012, he declared his intention to run for Governor of Ondo State under the platform of the [[Action Congress of Nigeria]] but he however came short of [[Oluwarotimi Odunayo Akeredolu|Rotimi Akeredolu]] who went on to represent the party as its aspirant.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://dailypost.ng/2012/05/10/ondo-governorship-poll-akande-tinubu-battle-over-acn-candidates-selection/|title=Ondo Governorship Poll:Akande, Tinubu battle over ACN candidate’s selection|work=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post Newspaper]]|last=Badejo|first=Abiodun|date=10 May 2012|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref>
He was one of the two aspirants under the platform of the [[All Progressives Congress]] who ran for the office of Governor at the 2016 Ondo State gubernatoral election, but lost out to [[Oluwarotimi Odunayo Akeredolu|Oluwarotimi Akeredolu]] at the primaries.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://worldstagegroup.com/index.php?active=news&newscid=27742&catid=8|title= Political thugs attack convoy of Segun Abraham, leading APC aspirant's for Ondo governorship election|work=World Stage News|last=Ponmile|first=Ayoola|date=10 February 2016|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://newtelegraphonline.com/boroffice-abraham-trade-words-attack/|title=Boroffice, Abraham trade words over attack|work=[[New Telegraph]]|last=Okeowo|first=Babatope|date=14 February 2016|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldstagegroup.com/index.php?active=news&newscid=31359&catid=8 |title=WorldStage News &#124; Ondo APC Primary: Abraham congratulates Akeredolu, promises to work for his victory |publisher=Worldstagegroup.com |date=4 September 2016 |author=Ayoola Ponmile|accessdate=2017-01-03}}</ref>
